    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-03-17T18:32:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-03-17T18:32:00-05:00" n="206"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d206">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">315/3–1753: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The United States Representative at the United Nations</hi>
                        (<persName corresp="#p_LODGEHCJ1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lodge</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">New York</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-03-17T18:32:00-05:00"
                            >March 17, 1953—6:32 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>565. Re <gloss target="#t_SYG1">SyG</gloss>. <persName corresp="#p_LODGEHCJ1"
                        >Lodge</persName> met with <persName corresp="#p_HOPPENOTH1"
                        >Hoppenot</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_JEBBSHMG1">Jebb</persName> at
                    their request in preparation for five-power consultation which will take place
                    18 March, 11 a.m.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_HOPPENOTH1">Hoppenot</persName> will preside over meeting.
                        <persName corresp="#p_JEBBSHMG1">Jebb</persName> will ask <persName
                        corresp="#p_ZORINVA1">Zorin</persName> if he has any reflections on closed
                        <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> meeting of March 13. He and <persName
                        corresp="#p_HOPPENOTH1">Hoppenot</persName> will attempt to draw out
                        <persName corresp="#p_ZORINVA1">Zorin</persName> as to Soviet intentions.
                    They think <persName corresp="#p_ZORINVA1">Zorin</persName> might come forward
                    with a new list of candidates which might include some or all of following:
                        <persName>Angel</persName> (Colombia), <persName corresp="#p_WWPWWKNB1"
                        >Wan</persName> (Thailand), <persName corresp="#p_PANDITMVL1"
                        >Pandit</persName> and <persName>Entezam</persName>.</p>
                <p>If new names are produced there will be no voting or decision on them and no
                    decisions will be taken by five powers. Intention then is to go forward with
                    next closed <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> meeting on 20 [<hi rend="italic"
                        >19</hi>] March at 3 p.m. without having further consultation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LODGEHCJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lodge</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
